owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

approvedToken(address).notice: tracks if token is approved to be deposited

depositsByAccountByToken(address,address.notice: tracks total deposits indexed by user and token

depositsByToken(address).notice: tracks total deposits indexed by token

feesCollectedByToken(address).notice: tracks total fees indexed by token

listApprovedTokens(uint256).notice: array of approved tokens to be deposited

michiBackpack().notice: instance of Michi Backpack (NFT that represents 6551 wallet)

documentation.text: @notice instance of Michi Backpack (NFT that represents 6551 wallet)
@notice tracks total deposits indexed by user and token
@notice tracks total deposits indexed by token
@notice tracks total fees indexed by token
@notice tracks if token is approved to be deposited
@notice array of approved tokens to be deposited
@notice emitted when a new Backpack is minted and corresponding 6551 wallet is initialized
@notice emitted when a Backpack receives a deposit
@notice error returned when a user tries to deposit an unauthorized token
@notice error returned when depositor is not the owner of 6551 wallet (safety precaution to prevent wrong deposits)
@notice error returned when 6551 wallet owner is not sender
@notice error returned when proposed deposit fee exceeds 5%
@notice error returned when proposed fee recipient is zero address
@notice error returned when attempting to add an already approved token
@notice error returned when attempting to remove an unapproved token
